# Phase 16: The Living Constraint System

## Goal
Implement the three engine constraints that transform `position` from a cosmetic label into a system with physical weight: **Rubber Band Effect (IDX-006)**, **Glacial Shift (IDX-007)**, and the **Temporal Simulation Harness** (the 10-tick headless loop test). Simultaneously introduce the new management-approved mechanics: Estate Velocity Memory, Perception Filter, and the ScenarioDef struct.

## Background & Management Ratification

Management has approved Phase 16 via RE: SOVEREIGN_DISPATCH_v16 (2026-03-04). All 8 injections accepted. Key architectural clarifications:

> *"Ensure the snap-back is handled as a velocity/vector force in chronos.rs, not a hard teleport. The rubber band should apply a massive gravitational pull back toward the center (Overton Window), bleeding Authority every turn they fight the current."*

> *"Store a historical array of the last 10 position coordinates and render a breadcrumb trail on the UI matrix."*

> *"If a Capitalist Estate sees the player moving Left by 0.1 points per tick, they grumble. If the player forces a 2.0 point jump Left in a single turn, the Capitalist Estate should immediately trigger a Capital Flight event."*

> *"Introduce a Perception Filter metric. The player might be orchestrating actions at (+3, -2) but spending Authority to keep the flavor_label anchored at (0, 0). If the Euclidean distance between Reality and Perception gets too wide, the illusion shatters."*

---

## Proposed Changes

### 1. [state.rs](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/state.rs) — IdeologyComponent Extended

#### [MODIFY] [state.rs](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/state.rs)

Add to [IdeologyComponent](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/state.rs#26-51):
```rust
/// The last 10 governing positions, oldest first. Used for breadcrumb UI trail
/// and for computing position_velocity. Updated each tick by chronos.rs.
pub position_history: Vec<(f64, f64)>,

/// Velocity vector: current_pos - prev_pos from last tick.
/// Used by Estate Velocity Memory to detect sudden acceleration events.
/// A jump of > 1.5 units/tick is treated as a "shock" by Estates.
pub position_velocity: (f64, f64),

/// The publicly projected position — what the sovereign *claims* to be.
/// Distinct from `position` (actual governing track record).
/// Spending Authority maintains the gap. If euclidean_distance(position, perceived_position)
/// exceeds a threshold, the Veil Shatters (Stability collapse event).
/// Cross-ref: METRIC_DEFINITIONS.md §12 (Perception Filter)
pub perceived_position: (f64, f64),

/// The flavor label for the *perceived* position — publicly broadcasted title.
/// May differ from flavor_label (actual) when Perception Filter is active.
pub perceived_flavor_label: String,
```

