### 2. [chronos.rs](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/chronos.rs) — Rubber Band & Glacial Shift

#### [MODIFY] [chronos.rs](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/chronos.rs)

**IDX-006: Rubber Band Effect (Gravitational Pull)**

On each tick, if `position` is outside the Overton Window Spread:
```
tension = euclidean_distance(position, center)
if tension > spread:
    pull_force = (tension - spread) * GRAVITY_CONSTANT   // e.g. 0.05
    position += normalize(center - position) * pull_force
    authority.current -= pull_force * AUTHORITY_BLEED     // e.g. 3.0 per unit
```

Key: this is **not a teleport**. It's a per-tick drift toward the center. The player pays Authority bleed every tick they hold an "unnatural" position. If they run out of AUT, the bleed converts to Stability loss.

**IDX-007: Glacial Shift**

Each tick, `position` drifts slightly toward [center](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/ideology_matrix.rs#344-349) proportional to Estate influence momentum:
```
drift_rate = 0.01 * (sum of estate influence shifts this tick)
position += normalize(center - position) * drift_rate
```

This means sustained Estate manipulation (e.g., slowly bleeding out the Labor Estate) produces gradual position movement without any Authority cost — it's the "earned" form of political drift.

**Estate Velocity Shock Detection:**

After computing `position_velocity` (delta from last tick):
```rust
let speed = euclidean_distance(prev_position, current_position);
if speed > 1.5 {
    // Inject Estate shock: trigger Capital Flight or equivalent zone gate
    // even if absolute position doesn't warrant it
}
```

**Position History Update:**

```rust
// Keep last 10 positions (shift window)
ideology.position_history.push(prev_position);
if ideology.position_history.len() > 10 {
    ideology.position_history.remove(0);
}
```

