### 3. [ideology_matrix.rs](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/ideology_matrix.rs) — Perception Filter Cost

#### [MODIFY] [ideology_matrix.rs](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/ideology_matrix.rs)

Add:
```rust
/// Computes the per-tick Authority cost to maintain a Perception Filter.
/// Cost scales with the Euclidean distance between real and perceived position.
/// At distance > VEIL_COLLAPSE_THRESHOLD, returns None (Veil shatters).
pub fn perception_maintenance_cost(
    real_pos: (f64, f64),
    perceived_pos: (f64, f64),
    base_cost: f64,
) -> Option<f64>

pub const VEIL_COLLAPSE_THRESHOLD: f64 = 3.5;
```

If [euclidean_distance(real, perceived) > VEIL_COLLAPSE_THRESHOLD](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/ideology_matrix.rs#124-137), return `None` — the engine fires a "Veil Shatters" event, causing Stability collapse. The reactor handles the event.

