### 4. New `scenario.rs` — ScenarioDef Struct

#### [NEW] [scenario.rs](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/scenario.rs)

Strictly typed scenario definition. Invalid files panic at engine boot, not during gameplay.

```rust
#[derive(Debug, Deserialize, Serialize)]
pub struct ScenarioDef {
    pub id: String,
    pub name: String,
    pub start_date: String,
    pub actors: HashMap<EntityId, ActorDef>,
}

#[derive(Debug, Deserialize, Serialize)]
pub struct ActorDef {
    pub starting_position: (f64, f64),    // validated: clamped to [-5, +5]
    pub factions: Vec<FactionDef>,
    pub estates: Vec<EstateDef>,
    pub authority_start: f64,
}
```

Validation at load time:
- `starting_position` coordinates must be in `[-5.0, +5.0]` — panic if not
- `faction.influence` values must sum to ~100 (within 1.0) — panic if not
- `estate.influence` values must sum to ~100 — panic if not

